Shared Middleware

Purpose: Reusable WebBroker middleware components that process HTTP requests and responses in a pipeline before reaching endpoint handlers.

What belongs here:
- Authentication middleware (token extraction, validation, user injection)
- CORS middleware (cross-origin header management)
- Request logging middleware (method, path, duration, status code)
- Rate limiting middleware (per-IP or per-token request throttling)
- Request timing and performance monitoring middleware
- Content type validation middleware (application/json enforcement)
- Request body size limiting middleware
- Compression middleware (gzip/deflate response encoding)

Middleware pattern: Each middleware should accept a TWebRequest, TWebResponse, and a next-handler reference. Middleware may short-circuit (return early) or pass to the next handler.

